Function to get L1 distance of any shared markers

In [2]:
get_l1_r_for_all_combination <- function(i, combos, markerlengths) {


  sample_a <- combos$a[i]
  sample_b <- combos$b[i]

  markerlength_tbl_a <- markerlengths %>%
      dplyr::filter(sample == sample_a)
  
 markerlength_tbl_b <- markerlengths %>%
     dplyr::filter(sample == sample_b)
 
 common_markers <- intersect(markerlength_tbl_a$marker, markerlength_tbl_b$marker)

  markerlengths_a  <- markerlength_tbl_a %>% 
    dplyr::filter(marker%in%common_markers) %>% 
    arrange(marker)  %>% 
    pull(length)

  markerlengths_b  <- markerlength_tbl_b %>% 
    dplyr::filter(marker%in%common_markers) %>% 
    arrange(marker)  %>% 
    pull(length)
  
  n_markers_a  <- length(markerlengths_a)
  n_markers_b  <- length(markerlengths_b)
  
  if (n_markers_a != n_markers_b) (error)
  
  l1  <- sum(abs(markerlengths_a - markerlengths_b))/n_markers_a
    
  list(a = sample_a, b = sample_b, l1 = l1, marker = n_markers_a)
  
}

markerlengths <- markerlengths_raw %>%
    group_by(subject, marker) %>%
    mutate(sample = ifelse(str_detect(sample, "B_C"), str_replace(sample, "B_C", "B_B"), sample)) %>%
    group_by(subject, sample, marker) %>%
    summarize(length=mean(length)) %>% 
    group_by(subject, marker) %>%
    mutate(length = length - length[sample==str_subset(sample, "B_B")[1]]) %>% 
    ungroup() %>% 
    drop_na()

In [23]:
save_mouse_hm <- function(subject_i) {

filtered_matrix <- markerlengths %>%
        filter(subject == subject_i) %>%
        group_by(marker)%>% 
        select(-subject) %>%
        pivot_wider(names_from = marker, 
        values_from = length) %>% 
        column_to_rownames("sample") %>%
        as.matrix()
    
    minmax <- max(abs(filtered_matrix), na.rm = TRUE)
    

    hm <- pheatmap::pheatmap(filtered_matrix,
        clustering_distance_rows = "manhattan",
        clustering_distance_cols = "manhattan",
        display_numbers = TRUE, number_color = "black", fontsize = 12,
        color = colorRampPalette(c("seagreen", "white", "purple3"))(42),
        na_col = "yellow", breaks = seq(-minmax, minmax, length.out = 43), 
        silent = TRUE
    )

ggsave(paste0("../plots/Figure2/", subject_i, "hm.pdf"), hm, height=7, width=14)

}

combos_wide <- combn(samples, m= 2) %>% as.data.frame()

## make combo table longer
combos_long <- data.frame(a=as.character(combos_wide[1,]), b=as.character(combos_wide[2,]))

## only use combintions from the same subject
combos <- combos_long %>% 
    mutate(sample_a=str_extract(a, "^[:upper:]+[:digit:]+"),
          sample_b=str_extract(b, "^[:upper:]+[:digit:]+"))  %>% 
    filter(sample_a==sample_b) %>% 
    dplyr::select(a, b)

l1_p <-  l1_tbl %>%
     filter(!str_detect(a, "_B_B"), !str_detect(b, "_B_B"), a %in% new_normal | b %in% new_normal) %>%
     mutate(
         sample = ifelse(a %in% new_normal, b, a),
         type = ifelse(str_detect(sample, "_H_"), "hsc", "crypt")
     )%>%
     mutate(divs = l1 / 9.43139014888478e-05) %>%
         wilcox_test(l1 ~ type) %>%
         p_format(add.p = TRUE, accuracy=1e-10) %>%
         add_xy_position()

pairwise_p <- l1_tbl %>%
     filter(!str_detect(a, "_B_B"), !str_detect(b, "_B_B")) %>%
     mutate(
         sample = ifelse(a %in% new_normal, b, a),
         type=case_when(
            str_detect(a, "_H_") & str_detect(b, "_H_") ~ "both_hsc",
            str_detect(a, "_C_") & str_detect(b, "_C_") ~ "both_crypt"
    ) )%>%
     drop_na() %>%
         mutate(type = fct_relevel(type, "both_hsc", "both_crypt")) %>%
         wilcox_test(l1 ~ type) %>%
         add_xy_position() %>%
         mutate(p=paste0("p=", p))
